Outdoors: yellow flowers, foliage and daylight are visible in soft focus. Young woman wears a cozy gray wool sweater and has dark brown, wavy hair. Natural light illuminates her workspace and her profile. She appears to be turning the page of the reference book, while reading.

Title: Silhouetted Laguna fisherman casts net at sunset
Caption: Silhouetted fisherman casts his net in shallow water at dusk. For over 100 years on a beach in Laguna, local fishermen have been working with wild bottlenose dolphins in a mutually beneficial relationship. During their collaborative partnership, dolphins drive shoals of mullet towards the waiting lines of fisherman who cast their nets when the dolphins signal by leaping out of the water. As the fish turn and flee from the nets they are caught by both dolphin and man. Location: Laguna, Santa Catarina, Brazil
